text.__SUMMARY__: The island worm snake (Typhlops sulcatus) is a species of snake in the Typhlopidae family.
text.Geographic range: It is believed to be endemic to southwestern Hispaniola including Navassa Island, an uninhabited island located in the Caribbean.
text.Conservation status:
Extinct on Navassa Island, where the species became a casualty of human interference and feral predators, such as rodents, cats, dogs and goats that were introduced during the large-scale mining period on this small island during the 1800s.
